article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 105, S. Dakota St. 96
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. -- Larry Wright and Travis Bader scored 22 points each to lift Oakland, Mich., over South Dakota State 105-96 on Saturday night. Keith Benson added a double-double with 18 points and 13 rebounds as the Golden Grizzlies (20-9,15-1 Summit) rolled to their 29th straight conference win at home. Oakland shot 54.3 percent from the field and were ahead by as many as 13 points late in the second half. Nate Wolters led the Jackrabbits (18-10,10-7Summit) with a game-high 29 points, shooting 11 of 24 from the field and 6 of 8 from the free-throw line. Jordan Dykstra added 25 points for the Jackrabbits, who shot 45.6 percent from the field, while Clint Sargent snagged a double-double with 17 points and 10 rebounds. Will Hudson added 17 points and Reggie Hamilton 14 for the Golden Grizzlies.
